<http://example.com/bizrisk> rdf:type owl:Ontology ;
    owl:versionIRI <http://example.com/bizrisk/0.1> ;
    <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/description> """
        Current ontology - BIZRISK - is described using W3C RDF Schema and the Web Ontology Language OWL.
        BIZRISK is built around the Cambridge Taxonomy of Business Risks: https://www.jbs.cam.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/crs-cambridge-taxonomy-of-business-risks.pdf
        It adds foundatonal classes and data properties to the taxonomy, using classes and properties from:
        - DOLCE as foundational ontology
        - The Business Model Risk ontology (BMRO), which is built on the Business Model Canvas

        This ontology is aiming to represent the following views:
        1. What risk events occurred to a company in the past, with what consequences, and how were they mitigated?
        2. What future risk events can occur to a company, with what consequences, and how can they be mitigated?

        Release Notes:
        - Version 0.1 Initial Release. Defines the main classes and data properties of the BIZRISK ontology

        """ ;
    <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/format> "application/rdf+xml" ;
    <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/rights> "Copyright Ã‚Â© 2023 - 2024 Open Risk" ;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor> "Vlad Radziuk, LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/vlad-radziuk-51318712a/" ;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> "Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 (CC BY 3.0)" ;
    dct:source "Cambridge Centre for Risk Studies (2019). Cambridge Taxonomy of Business Risks." ;
    rdfs:comment "..." ;
    rdfs:label "A Business Risks Ontology" ;
